            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>PutCursorPosition</Bold> - PutCursorPosition provides a way to save the cursor position in an array so you can come back to it later without having to find the original image again. Here are the columns:
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph FontSize="14pt" >
                <Italic>
                    <Bold>
                        1. Sequence
                    </Bold>
                </Italic>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                Sequence is a decimal number with 4 digits after the decimal. It can be modified to allow you to insert rows anywhere in your script. Rows are executed in sequence number order.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph FontSize="14pt" >
                <Italic>
                    <Bold>
                        2. Verb
                    </Bold>
                </Italic>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                PutCursorPosition
            </Paragraph>


            <Paragraph FontSize="14pt" >
                <Italic>
                    <Bold>
                        3. Entity1
                    </Bold>
                </Italic>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                Entity1 is the name of a array that has been defined in the Arrays tab. PutCursorPosition puts the X and Y coordinates of the cursor into the array.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph FontSize="14pt" >
